  "description": "Geothermal energy harnesses heat from the Earth's interior via natural hydrothermal manifestations or drilled wells. Provides continuous baseload power at 90-95% capacity factor — the highest of any renewable. Three tiers: direct-use heating (shallow wells), hydrothermal flash/dry steam power generation (deep wells driving turbines), and ground-source heat pumps (shallow ground as heat source/sink).",
